{"key":"post-13208576","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13208576</id>\n<content>I'd put it to one side rather than on top.&amp;nbsp; This gets it closer to the substrate, which is where it matters.&amp;nbsp; Disregard bad advice that mushrooms don't need much light.&amp;nbsp; They do.&amp;nbsp; If one is comparing to plants, they don't need as much as growing pot, but they do need bright light to develop to the full finish weight you're looking for.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The amount of light received by the mycelium decreases by the square of the distance, so get it as close as possible without excessive heating of the terrarium.&amp;nbsp; Put it on a timer for 12/12.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13208580</next>\n<prev>13208508</prev>\n<first>13208461</first>\n<last>13208601</last>\n<when>1284735185</when>\n<utime>09/17/10 05:53 PM</utime>\n</post>"}